\cf6 \cb7 > What are feature flags? \cf2 \cb1 \
\
\cf6 \uc0\u9210 \cf2  Feature flags are props that turn features on or off in a component. Instead of having two separate\
  components, you have one component with optional features controlled by props.\
\
  
\f1\b Example from our Memory Cards:
\f0\b0 \
\
  
\f1\b Current situation
\f0\b0  (two separate components):\
  \cf10 // ArchiveMemoryCard - has all the features\cf2 \
  <ArchiveMemoryCard\
    memory=\{memory\}\
    onSelect=\{handleSelect\}\
    selectMode=\{\cf12 true\cf2 \}\
    \cf10 // ... lots of props\cf2 \
  />\
\
  \cf10 // MemoryCard - simple display only\cf2 \
  \cf14 <\cf12 MemoryCard\cf14  \cf2 \
  \cf14   \cf15 memory\cf14 =\cf11 \{memory\}\cf2 \
  \cf14   \cf15 isStackedView\cf14 =\cf11 \{false\}\cf2 \
  \cf14 />\cf2 \
\
  
\f1\b With feature flags
\f0\b0  (one consolidated component):\
  \cf10 // In Archive - turn on all the features\cf2 \
  <MemoryCard\
    memory=\{memory\}\
    selectMode=\{\cf12 true\cf2 \}              \cf10 // \uc0\u8592  feature flag\cf2 \
    showConstellation=\{\cf12 true\cf2 \}       \cf10 // \uc0\u8592  feature flag\cf2 \
    draggable=\{\cf12 true\cf2 \}               \cf10 // \uc0\u8592  feature flag\cf2 \
    onSelect=\{handleSelect\}\
    onHashtagClick=\{handleClick\}\
  />\
\
  \cf10 // In Conspiracy Board - simple mode\cf2 \
  \cf14 <\cf12 MemoryCard\cf14  \cf2 \
  \cf14   \cf15 memory\cf14 =\cf11 \{memory\}\cf2 \
  \cf14   \cf15 isStackedView\cf14 =\cf11 \{true\}\cf14            // \uc0\u8592  \cf15 feature\cf14  \cf15 flag\cf2 \
  \cf14   // \cf15 All\cf14  \cf15 other\cf14  \cf15 flags\cf14  \cf15 default\cf14  \cf15 to\cf14  \cf15 false\cf2 \
  \cf14 />\cf2 \
\
  Inside the component, you'd have code like:\
  \cf12 export\cf2  \cf12 default\cf2  \cf12 function\cf13  MemoryCard(\{ \cf2 \
  \cf13   memory, \cf2 \
  \cf13   selectMode = \cf12 false\cf13 ,           \cf11 //\cf13  \uc0\u8592  defaults to \cf12 false\cf2 \
  \cf13   showConstellation = \cf12 false\cf13 ,    \cf11 //\cf13  \uc0\u8592  defaults to \cf12 false\cf2 \
  \cf13   draggable = \cf12 false\cf13 ,\cf2 \
  \cf13   isStackedView = \cf12 false\cf13 ,\cf2 \
  \cf13   ...\cf2 \
  \cf13 \}) \cf2 \{\
    \cf12 return\cf2  (\
      \cf14 <\cf12 div\cf14  \cf15 className\cf14 =\cf11 "memory-card"\cf14 >\cf2 \
        \{/* Always show title */\}\
        \cf14 <\cf12 div\cf14  \cf15 className\cf14 =\cf11 "memory-card-title"\cf14 >\cf2 \{memory.title\}\cf14 </\cf12 div\cf14 >\cf2 \
\
        \{/* Only show if feature flag is enabled */\}\
        \{selectMode && (\
          \cf14 <\cf12 div\cf14  \cf15 className\cf14 =\cf11 "memory-checkbox"\cf14  \cf15 onClick\cf14 =\cf11 \{onSelect\}\cf14  />\cf2 \
        )\}\
\
        \{/* Only show if feature flag is enabled */\}\
        \{showConstellation && hasConnections(memory.id) && (\
          \cf14 <\cf12 ConstellationIcon\cf14  />\cf2 \
        )\}\
\
        \{/* Different rendering based on flag */\}\
        \{isStackedView ? (\
          \cf14 <\cf12 div\cf14  \cf15 className\cf14 =\cf11 "stacked-view"\cf14 >\cf2 \{/* mini card */\}\cf14 </\cf12 div\cf14 >\cf2 \
        ) : (\
          \cf14 <\cf12 div\cf14  \cf15 className\cf14 =\cf11 "full-view"\cf14 >\cf2 \{/* full card */\}\cf14 </\cf12 div\cf14 >\cf2 \
        )\}\
      \cf14 </\cf12 div\cf14 >\cf2 \
    )\
  \}\
\
  
\f1\b Benefits:
\f0\b0 \
  - \uc0\u9989  Single source of truth for styling\
  - \uc0\u9989  Consistent appearance everywhere\
  - \uc0\u9989  Easier to maintain (one component vs two)\
