\f1\b What it does:
\f0\b0 \
\
  
\f1\b Memory titles
\f0\b0  in your app are stored like:\
  "phrase1 \'95 phrase2 \'95 phrase3"\
  (Multiple phrases separated by bullet points)\
\
  
\f1\b The formatter transforms them for display:
\f0\b0 \
\
  \cf16 Normal View:\cf2 \
\
  "phrase1 \'95 phrase2 \'95 phrase3"\
  Just cleans up any \cf9 <br>\cf2  tags, keeps the bullets\
\
  \cf16 Simplified View (condensed cards):\cf2 \
\
  phrase1\
  \'97\
  phrase2\
  \'97\
  phrase3\
  Takes only the 
\f1\b first 3 phrases
\f0\b0 , separates them with em dashes (\cf9 \'97\cf2 ) and line breaks\
\
  
\f1\b Example:
\f0\b0 \
\
  If a memory title is stored as:\
  "Morning coffee \'95 Read newspaper \'95 Call Mom \'95 Walk dog"\
\
  
\f1\b Normal view
\f0\b0  shows:\
  Morning coffee \'95 Read newspaper \'95 Call Mom \'95 Walk dog\
\
  
\f1\b Simplified view
\f0\b0  shows:\
  Morning coffee\
  \'97\
  Read newspaper\
  \'97\
  Call Mom\
  (Only first 3, stacked vertically with dashes)\
\
  ---\
  This is used in both Archive and Conspiracy Board when you click the "condense/simplify" button. It's\
  
\f1\b optional
\f0\b0  - if you don't pass it, the component uses its own default formatting.\
